messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 6/13/03 12:17:23 PM, KathrynJB@... writes:

<< >
> Here they have purple cowgirl boots
>
>

Yes, and they're a thousand dollars. I don't love Beth that much. LOL >>

If they don't have to be cowgirl boots, but can be other kinds of boots,
check here:

http://www.highfiber.com/~bohemond/Bootshop/bio.html



That's one of my husband's former squires, and he plays cello with us once a
week or so. He lives in our old house (rents/fixes the house we lived in for
20 years, until five or six years ago).

They're NOT $1000 (more like $250 to $300) and I know he can get purple
leather at The Leather Factory here in town, and the extra would be based on the
extra cost, I suppose. You could also learn to make your own boots, but by the
time you get the tools and you practice on a few pairs... better to buy some.

Or you could just get a really good photo of you, adobe-photoshop some GREAT
purple boots with gold threads and silver fittings, and have it blown up,
framed, and put on the wall. Cheaper. <g>

Sandra
